{
 "cells": [

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cef20583",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Genarating the Wireless Channel for Indoor Open Office Terrain\n",
    "The channel models has been designed to support the following features:\n",
    "\n",
    "|Parameters|Values|\n",
    "| :- | -:  |\n",
    "| Antenna Array  | [$\\text{M}_g, \\text{N}_g, \\text{M}, \\text{N}, \\text{P}$]  |\n",
    "| UE Antenna Array  | [1,1,2,2,1]  |\n",
    "| UE Antenna  | Omni  |\n",
    "| BS Antenna Array  | [1,1,4,4,1]  |\n",
    "| BS Antenna  | Parabolic  |\n",
    "| Carrier Frequency  | $3 \\times 10^9$  |\n",
    "| Simulation Layout | Rectangular |\n",
    "| Subcarrier Spacing | 30 kHz|\n",
    "| fftsize | 512 |\n",
    "| Terrain | Indoor-Factory (InF-SL) |\n",
    "| Mobility | Disabled |\n",
    "| Inter-site Distance | 20 |\n",
    "| Number of Sectors Site | 3 |\n",
    "| UE Height | Uniform$(0,1)$ m |\n",
    "| UE Drop | Random |\n",
    "| UE Height Distribution | Random |\n",
    "| BS Height       | 3m  |\n",
    "| Ceiling Height  | 6m  |\n",
    "| clutter Height  | 4m  |\n",
    "| clutter Size    | 3m  |\n",
    "| clutter Density | 0.4 |\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "In this Tutorial, we will generate the Multicell MIMO channel between multiple users and multiple base-stations for **Indoor Factory Terrain**. THe content of the tutorial is listed below:\n",
    "\n",
    "**Table of Contents**\n",
    "\n",
    "* [Import Libraries](#Import-Libraries)\n",
    "    - [Python Libraries](#Python-Libraries)\n",
    "    - [5G Toolkit Libraries](#5G-Toolkit-Libraries)\n",
    "* [Simulation Parameters](#Simulation-Parameters)\n",
    "* [Generate Antenna Arrays](#Generate-Antenna-Array)\n",
    "* [Node Mobility/Route](#Node-Mobility)\n",
    "* [Generate Simulation Topology](#Generate-Simulation-Layout)\n",
    "* [Generate Channel(LSP/SSPs) Parameters](#Generate-Channel-Parameters)\n",
    "* [Generate Channel Coefficients](#Generate-Channel-Coefficients)\n",
    "* [Generate OFDM Channel Generation](#Generate-OFDM-Channel)\n",
    "    - [Frequency Domain: Magnitude Response Plot](#Frequency-Domain-:-Magnitude-Response-Plot)\n",
    "    - [Time Domain Channel Response](#Time-Domain-Channel-response)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9460892c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Import Libraries\n",
    "\n",
    "### Import Python Libraries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "4d2e1a7a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "os.environ[\"CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES\"] = \"-1\"\n",
    "os.environ['TF_CPP_MIN_LOG_LEVEL'] = '3' \n",
    "\n",
    "# %matplotlib widget\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import matplotlib as mpl\n",
    "import numpy      as np"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "65bdbcf6",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Import 5G Toolkit Libraries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "74d30da7",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import sys\n",
    "sys.path.append(\"../../../\")\n",
    "\n",
    "from toolkit5G.ChannelModels import NodeMobility\n",
    "from toolkit5G.ChannelModels import AntennaArrays\n",
    "from toolkit5G.ChannelModels import SimulationLayout\n",
    "from toolkit5G.ChannelModels import ParameterGenerator\n",
    "from toolkit5G.ChannelModels import ChannelGenerator"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "947357fb",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Simulation Parameters"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "8055441f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The simulation parameters are defined as follows\n",
    "  * ``propTerrain`` defines propagation scenario or terrain for BS-UE links\n",
    "  * ``carrierFrequency`` defines carrier frequency in Hz\n",
    "  * ``nBSs`` defines number of Base Stations (BSs)\n",
    "  * ``nUEs`` defines number of User Equipments (UEs) \n",
    "  * ``nSnapShots`` defines number of SnapShots"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "eff4a8e1",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Simulation Parameters\n",
    "propTerrain      = \"InH-OO\"      # Propagation Scenario or Terrain for BS-UE links\n",
    "carrierFrequency = 3.6*10**9                   # carrier frequency in Hz\n",
    "BSgeometry       = np.array([6,2])           # number of BSs along rows and columns\n",
    "nBSs             = np.product(BSgeometry)    # number of BSs \n",
    "nUEs             = 50                        # number of UEs \n",
    "nSnapShots       = 1                         # number of SnapShots"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e66f7706",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Generate Antenna Arrays"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6d1e0176",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The following steps describe the procedure to simulate AntennaArrays Objects at a single carrier frequency\n",
    "both at Tx and Rx side:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "2e7f555e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 960x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Antenna Array at UE side\n",
    "# assuming antenna element type to be \"OMNI\"\n",
    "# with 2 panel and 2 single polarized antenna element per panel.\n",
    "\n",
    "ueAntArray = AntennaArrays(antennaType     = \"OMNI\", \n",
    "                           centerFrequency = carrierFrequency,\n",
    "                           arrayStructure  = np.array([1,1,2,2,1]))\n",
    "ueAntArray() \n",
    "# Radiation Pattern of Rx antenna element \n",
    "fig, ax = ueAntArray.displayAntennaRadiationPattern()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "c750f345",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 960x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Antenna Array at BS side\n",
    "# assuming antenna element type to be \"3GPP_38.901\", a parabolic antenna \n",
    "# with 4 panel and 4 single polarized antenna element per panel.\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "bsAntArray = AntennaArrays(antennaType     = \"3GPP_38.901\", \n",
    "                           centerFrequency = carrierFrequency,\n",
    "                           arrayStructure  = np.array([1,1,4,4,1]))\n",
    "bsAntArray()\n",
    "# Radiation Pattern of Tx antenna element \n",
    "fig, ax = bsAntArray.displayAntennaRadiationPattern()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "52755c9b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Generate Simulation Layout\n",
    "\n",
    "We define the simulation topology parametes:\n",
    "\n",
    " - ``ISD``: Inter Site Distance\n",
    " - ``minDist``: Minimum distance between transmitter and receiver.\n",
    " - ``bsHt``: BS heights \n",
    " - ``ueHt``: UE heights\n",
    " - ``topology``: Simulation Topology\n",
    " - ``nSectorsPerSite``: Number of Sectors Per Site\n",
    " \n",
    "Furthermore, users can access and update following parameters as per their requirements for channel using the handle simLayoutObj.x where x is:\n",
    "\n",
    " - The following parameters can be accessed or updated immendiately after object creation\n",
    "    - ``UEtracks``\n",
    "    - ``UELocations``\n",
    "    - ``ueOrientation``\n",
    "    - ``UEvelocityVector``\n",
    "    - ``BStracks``\n",
    "    - ``BSLocations``\n",
    "    - ``bsOrientation``\n",
    "    - ``BSvelocityVector``\n",
    "    \n",
    " - The following parameters can be accessed or updated after calling the object\n",
    "    - ``linkStateVec``\n",
    "    "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "c811937a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.legend.Legend at 0x7f73c2c5ea10>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 6,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Layout Parameters\n",
    "isd                  = 20         # inter site distance in meters\n",
    "minDist              = 0          # min distance between each UE and BS in meters\n",
    "ueHt                 = 1          # UE height in meters\n",
    "ceilingHt            = 6          # height of ceiling in meters\n",
    "clutterHt            = 4          # height of clutter for indoor factory scenario\n",
    "clutterSize          = 3         # size of clutter for indoor factory scenario\n",
    "clutterDen           = 0.4        # density of clutter for indoor factory scenario\n",
    "bsHt                 = 3   # BS height in meters\n",
    "bslayoutType         = \"Rectangular\" # BS layout type\n",
    "ueDropType           = \"Rectangular\" # UE drop type\n",
    "nSectorsPerSite      = 1             # number of sectors per site\n",
    "indoorUEfract        = 1             # Fraction of UEs located indoor\n",
    "htDist               = \"random\"      # UE height distribution\n",
    "ueDist               = \"random\"      # UE Distribution per site\n",
    "lengthOfIndoorObject = 3             # length of indoor object typically having rectangular geometry \n",
    "widthOfIndoorObject  = 3             # width of indoor object\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "simLayoutObj = SimulationLayout(numOfBS = BSgeometry,\n",
    "                                numOfUE = nUEs,\n",
    "                                heightOfBS = bsHt,\n",
    "                                heightOfUE = ueHt, \n",
    "                                ISD = isd,\n",
    "                                layoutType = bslayoutType,\n",
    "                                ueDropMethod = ueDropType, \n",
    "                                UEdistibution = ueDist,\n",
    "                                UEheightDistribution = htDist,\n",
    "                                numOfSectorsPerSite = nSectorsPerSite,\n",
    "                                minUEBSDistance = minDist)\n",
    "simLayoutObj(terrain = propTerrain, \n",
    "             carrierFreq = carrierFrequency,\n",
    "             ueAntennaArray = ueAntArray,\n",
    "             bsAntennaArray = bsAntArray,                 \n",
    "             indoorUEfraction = indoorUEfract,\n",
    "             heightOfRoom = ceilingHt,\n",
    "             clutterHeight = clutterHt,\n",
    "             clutterSize = clutterSize, \n",
    "             clutterDensity = clutterDen)\n",
    "# displaying the topology of simulation layout\n",
    "fig, ax = simLayoutObj.display2DTopology(refBS=0)\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel(\"x-coordinates (m)\")\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel(\"y-coordinates (m)\")\n",
    "ax.set_title(\"Simulation Topology\")\n",
    "ax.legend()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c06b16cb",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Generate Channel Parameters\n",
    "\n",
    "* This subsection provides the steps to obtain all the cluster level channel parameters, which includes both `Large Scale Parameters (LSPs)`\n",
    "  and `Small Scale Parameters (SSPs)`. \n",
    "* LSPs includes `Path Loss (PL)`, `Delay Spread (DS)` and `Angular Spreads` both in Azimuth and Zenith directions,\n",
    "  and `cluster powers (Pn)` comes under SSPs.\n",
    "  \n",
    "- LSPs/SSPs: paramGenObj.x where x is\n",
    "    - ``linkStateVec``\n",
    "    - ``delaySpread``\n",
    "    - ``phiAoA_LoS``, ``phiAoA_mn``, ``phiAoA_spread``\n",
    "    - ``thetaAoA_LoS``, ``thetaAoA_mn``, ``thetaAoA_spread``\n",
    "    - ``phiAoD_LoS``, ``phiAoD_mn``, ``phiAoD_spread``\n",
    "    - ``thetaAoD_LoS``, ``thetaAoD_mn``, ``thetaAoD_spread``\n",
    "    - ``xpr``\n",
    "    - ``pathloss``, ``pathDelay``, ``pathPower``\n",
    "    - ``shadowFading``"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "d3af3e18",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# channel parameters\n",
    "paramGenObj = simLayoutObj.getParameterGenerator()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "835cd549",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Generate Channel Coefficients\n",
    "\n",
    "Cluster level channel coefficients can be simulated using the following code snippet.\n",
    "\n",
    " - ``channel.coefficients`` with shape: `(number of carrier frequencies, number of snapshots, number of BSs, number of UEs, numCluster/numPaths, number of Rx antennas, number of Tx antennas)`\n",
    " - ``channel.delays`` with shape: `(number of carrier frequencies, number of snapshots, number of BSs, number of UEs, numCluster/numPaths)`\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "679a99da",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(1, 1, 12, 50, 23, 4, 16)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 8,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "channel = paramGenObj.getChannel(applyPathLoss = True)\n",
    "channel.coefficients.shape"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c7d5292a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Generate OFDM Channel\n",
    "\n",
    "- Shape of OFDM Channel:\n",
    "    - `Hf` is of shape : ``(number of carrier frequencies, number of snapshots, number of BSs, number of UEs, fftsize, number of Rx antennas, number of Tx antennas)``"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "7523084c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(1, 1, 12, 50, 1024, 4, 16)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 9,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fftsize = 1024\n",
    "Hf = channel.ofdm(30*10**3, fftsize, simLayoutObj.carrierFrequency)\n",
    "Hf.shape"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "61732285",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Frequency Domain : Magnitude Response Plot\n",
    "\n",
    "* The frequency domain magnitude plots (frequency responses) helps demonstate the order of frequency selectivity\n",
    "    - Frequency selectivity is low for LOS Channel\n",
    "    - frequency selectivity is high for NLOS Channels\n",
    "    \n",
    "* Wireless channel at high frequency\n",
    "    - has higher path-loss\n",
    "    - less frequency selective (due to lower delay spread and weak distance paths)\n",
    "    \n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "a8a29f4c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1750x750 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "scaleFig = 1\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(17.5/scaleFig,7.5/scaleFig))\n",
    "\n",
    "i = 0\n",
    "ax[0].plot(np.arange(-channel.fftSize/2, channel.fftSize/2)*channel.subCarrierSpacing + channel.fc[0], \n",
    "           np.abs(Hf[0,0,0,i,:,0,0]), \"g\", label = \"$f_c$=\"+str(channel.fc[0]/10**9)+\" GHz\")\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "ax[0].legend()\n",
    "ax[0].set_xlabel(\"Frequency (Hz)\")\n",
    "ax[0].set_ylabel(\"Magnitude Response\")\n",
    "ax[0].set_title(\"Channel Magnitude Response\")\n",
    "ax[0].grid()\n",
    "\n",
    "ax[1].plot(np.arange(-channel.fftSize/2, channel.fftSize/2)*channel.subCarrierSpacing + channel.fc[0], \n",
    "           np.angle(Hf[0,0,0,i,:,0,0]), \"g\", label = \"$f_c$=\"+str(channel.fc[0]/10**9)+\" GHz\")\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "ax[1].legend()\n",
    "ax[1].set_xlabel(\"Frequency (Hz)\")\n",
    "ax[1].set_ylabel(\"Phase Response\")\n",
    "ax[1].grid()\n",
    "ax[1].set_title(\"Channel Phase Response\")\n",
    "\n",
    "fig.suptitle(\"Channel Frequency Response: Phase and Magnitude\")\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "92d930c1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Time Domain Channel response\n",
    "\n",
    "- Practical wireless channel are bandlimited which results in:\n",
    "    - impulses widening:\n",
    "        - higher for lower frequency channels\n",
    "    - time spread\n",
    "    \n",
    "These effects can be observed in following plots."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "9bae3e83",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 875x375 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "ht = np.fft.ifft(Hf, fftsize, axis = -3, norm = \"ortho\")\n",
    "\n",
    "scaleFig = 2\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(17.5/scaleFig,7.5/scaleFig))\n",
    "i = 0\n",
    "ax.stem(channel.delays[0,0,0,i], np.abs(channel.coefficients[0,0,0,i,:,0,0]), \"r\", label = \"Ideal Channel\")\n",
    "ax.stem(np.arange(channel.fftSize)/(channel.fftSize*channel.subCarrierSpacing), np.abs(ht[0,0,0,i,:,0,0]), \"g\", label = \"Practical Channel\")\n",
    "ax.legend()\n",
    "ax.set_xlim([0, 0.2*10**-5])\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel(\"delays (s)\")\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel(\"Power\")\n",
    "ax.grid()\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "fig.suptitle(\"Power Delay Profile for the Different Carrier Frequencies\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
